1
00:01:35,680 --> 00:01:39,680
From the expectant eyes of everyone

2
00:01:40,120 --> 00:01:42,440
who donated to the War of Resistance Against Japanese Aggression,

3
00:01:42,440 --> 00:01:44,680
and from the angry eyes of everyone

4
00:01:44,720 --> 00:01:46,400
who was humiliated by the Japanese,

5
00:01:46,400 --> 00:01:48,360
I can feel that immense power.

6
00:01:48,960 --> 00:01:50,280
That is exactly what we seek,

7
00:01:50,280 --> 00:01:51,680
and what we expect:

8
00:01:52,440 --> 00:01:54,370
the awakening of the whole nation,

9
00:01:55,039 --> 00:01:59,240
the awakening and cohesion of every heart.

10
00:02:02,040 --> 00:02:03,900
As Comrade Mao Zedong of our party

11
00:02:04,000 --> 00:02:05,930
mentioned in "On Protracted War",

12
00:02:06,560 --> 00:02:11,200
the War of Resistance Against Japanese Aggression is a spectacle in the history of war,

13
00:02:11,200 --> 00:02:13,400
a feat of the Chinese nation,

14
00:02:14,720 --> 00:02:17,079
and an earth-shattering great cause.

15
00:02:17,400 --> 00:02:21,120
This spectacle, feat, and great cause

16
00:02:21,160 --> 00:02:22,240
expect even more

17
00:02:22,440 --> 00:02:24,840
that national entrepreneurs like Mr. Tian

18
00:02:25,240 --> 00:02:26,640
can work together with us

19
00:02:26,920 --> 00:02:29,280
in the same trench to accomplish it.

20
00:02:30,079 --> 00:02:32,079
All I can think of is a few words:

21
00:02:32,680 --> 00:02:34,200
At the worst,

22
00:02:36,120 --> 00:02:37,600
actively change.

23
00:02:48,400 --> 00:02:52,120
At the worst, actively change.

24
00:02:55,240 --> 00:02:56,300
I've learned a lot.

25
00:02:59,760 --> 00:03:00,760
I'm leaving first. You wash first.

26
00:03:00,760 --> 00:03:01,920
Okay.

27
00:03:04,440 --> 00:03:05,480
Commander Zhang,

28
00:03:05,800 --> 00:03:07,260
you're not doing it right.

29
00:03:07,280 --> 00:03:08,210
Do you need help?

30
00:03:08,240 --> 00:03:09,040
Miss Xiaoyue,

31
00:03:09,120 --> 00:03:09,720
No, thanks.

32
00:03:09,720 --> 00:03:10,360
Haven't eaten yet?

33
00:03:10,360 --> 00:03:10,820
Not yet.

34
00:03:10,880 --> 00:03:11,880
I can do it myself.

35
00:03:11,960 --> 00:03:13,760
Uncle Liu, you went to the field.

36
00:03:16,320 --> 00:03:17,800
You must be tired. Time to eat.

37
00:03:17,800 --> 00:03:18,440
Not tired.

38
00:03:19,520 --> 00:03:21,180
I'm just learning how to farm,

39
00:03:21,440 --> 00:03:22,800
I'm not very skilled at it yet.

40
00:03:22,800 --> 00:03:24,160
Farming is not difficult.

41
00:03:24,160 --> 00:03:26,200
Just remember a few formulas.

42
00:03:27,280 --> 00:03:28,720
Come, go eat.

43
00:03:28,800 --> 00:03:29,800
Give it to me.

44
00:03:33,160 --> 00:03:34,800
Come, time to eat, Huangdou.

45
00:03:38,320 --> 00:03:41,160
Hoe deep in spring, shallow in summer,

46
00:03:41,520 --> 00:03:44,000
hoe like shaving your face in autumn.

47
00:03:44,880 --> 00:03:46,880
Cotton won't die from the sun,

48
00:03:47,520 --> 00:03:49,380
pumpkins won't die from the rain,

49
00:03:49,560 --> 00:03:51,120
cabbage won't drown,

50
00:03:51,360 --> 00:03:53,290
and onions won't die from drought.

51
00:04:07,360 --> 00:04:08,040
Sir,

52
00:04:09,200 --> 00:04:11,080
when can Ms. Zeng be sent away?

53
00:04:11,200 --> 00:04:11,920
Tonight.

54
00:04:12,400 --> 00:04:15,160
The route to send her out of Shanghai is all arranged.

55
00:04:15,160 --> 00:04:16,160
Then what about

56
00:04:16,399 --> 00:04:19,079
those Japanese spies hanging around outside our house?

57
00:04:19,079 --> 00:04:20,720
They change shifts at seven o'clock tonight.

58
00:04:20,720 --> 00:04:21,839
I will use this time

59
00:04:21,920 --> 00:04:24,280
to hide Ms. Zeng in the swill bucket and send her out.

60
00:04:24,280 --> 00:04:26,240
Ms. Zeng will hide at the bottom of the swill bucket,

61
00:04:26,240 --> 00:04:29,040
and there will be three inches of swill on the load-bearing plate above her head.

62
00:04:29,040 --> 00:04:30,640
I will personally escort her to the dock

63
00:04:30,640 --> 00:04:32,920
and watch her get on the boat. Don't worry.

64
00:04:32,920 --> 00:04:34,680
If I can't trust you,

65
00:04:35,800 --> 00:04:37,320
there's no one I can trust.

66
00:04:37,440 --> 00:04:39,770
Actually, smuggling a person isn't hard.

67
00:04:39,840 --> 00:04:41,440
The key is that no one can know

68
00:04:41,480 --> 00:04:43,140
that you're involved in this.

69
00:04:43,280 --> 00:04:45,010
I also had to ask a lot of people.

70
00:04:46,960 --> 00:04:48,280
Thanks for your hard work, Brother Qi.

71
00:04:48,280 --> 00:04:49,120
It's my duty.

72
00:04:49,400 --> 00:04:51,060
I'll go as soon as it gets dark.

73
00:04:55,800 --> 00:04:56,440
Sir,

74
00:04:56,760 --> 00:04:58,090
stay with me for a while.

75
00:04:58,200 --> 00:04:59,760
It's not even dark yet.

76
00:05:15,840 --> 00:05:19,280
I remember you said you know an

77
00:05:19,680 --> 00:05:21,960
international adventurer named... what was it?

78
00:05:21,960 --> 00:05:22,600
Orlando.

79
00:05:22,880 --> 00:05:23,600
Orlando.

80
00:05:24,320 --> 00:05:25,120
Are you familiar with him?

81
00:05:25,120 --> 00:05:26,180
I've met him twice.

82
00:05:26,400 --> 00:05:28,000
He is a Swiss Jew

83
00:05:28,080 --> 00:05:29,920
who has been making money in Shanghai for years.

84
00:05:29,920 --> 00:05:32,040
That guy is a bit crazy

85
00:05:32,360 --> 00:05:33,560
and a desperado.

86
00:05:36,159 --> 00:05:38,159
He's the one who helped the Liu family's woolen mill

87
00:05:38,159 --> 00:05:39,200
smuggle things out.

88
00:05:39,200 --> 00:05:40,920
Yes. According to him,

89
00:05:41,240 --> 00:05:42,840
he bribed a Major General

90
00:05:42,840 --> 00:05:45,640
at the Japanese Army headquarters to clear the way,

91
00:05:45,640 --> 00:05:48,200
allowing him to sneak into the Liu family's military-controlled warehouse

92
00:05:48,200 --> 00:05:50,330
and smuggle out a lot of raw materials.

93
00:05:52,760 --> 00:05:53,480
Master.

94
00:05:54,159 --> 00:05:57,200
You're not thinking of asking him to smuggle things, are you?

95
00:05:57,200 --> 00:05:58,800
That would be too dangerous.

96
00:06:00,640 --> 00:06:02,360
Isn't it dangerous now?

97
00:06:05,520 --> 00:06:06,880
I heard the Liu family mention

98
00:06:06,880 --> 00:06:09,360
that Orlando is asking for an exorbitant price,

99
00:06:09,360 --> 00:06:10,890
frighteningly expensive.

100
00:06:12,560 --> 00:06:14,090
Frighteningly expensive.

101
00:06:16,680 --> 00:06:18,280
Then we'll choose the most expensive one.

102
00:06:18,280 --> 00:06:19,360
What do you mean?

103
00:06:19,680 --> 00:06:21,800
Are you thinking of smuggling the machinery factory?

104
00:06:21,800 --> 00:06:23,840
The machinery factory can't be dismantled.

105
00:06:23,840 --> 00:06:25,880
The machinery factory is the root of Tailai.

106
00:06:25,880 --> 00:06:29,080
If the machinery factory is dismantled, what will you do?

107
00:06:29,480 --> 00:06:30,560
I'm just thinking about it.

108
00:06:30,560 --> 00:06:31,360
Master,

109
00:06:31,680 --> 00:06:34,010
you absolutely cannot have this thought.

110
00:06:34,200 --> 00:06:37,120
Qi, you're talking a bit too much today.

111
00:06:46,680 --> 00:06:47,960
Don't look so gloomy.

112
00:06:49,240 --> 00:06:50,120
Smile.

113
00:06:51,320 --> 00:06:51,880
Smile.

114
00:06:55,800 --> 00:06:57,400
Cry. Cry.

115
00:07:15,360 --> 00:07:17,560
Don't look. This thing hurts your eyes.

116
00:07:18,640 --> 00:07:20,170
Can this pile of scrap metal

117
00:07:20,200 --> 00:07:21,680
make this broken car run?

118
00:07:23,040 --> 00:07:24,600
What I'm making is a charcoal car,

119
00:07:24,600 --> 00:07:25,800
also called a gas car.

120
00:07:26,440 --> 00:07:28,700
It's about installing all the equipment

121
00:07:29,000 --> 00:07:30,400
on a regular car.

122
00:07:30,600 --> 00:07:32,600
The most important part is this thing,

123
00:07:32,600 --> 00:07:35,280
called a gas generator.

124
00:07:35,680 --> 00:07:38,360
You put all the charcoal in here.

125
00:07:38,800 --> 00:07:41,200
After the charcoal burns, it produces gas,

126
00:07:41,360 --> 00:07:43,320
which can replace regular fuel

127
00:07:43,880 --> 00:07:45,280
and make the engine work.

128
00:07:46,720 --> 00:07:49,320
Mr. Zhang is also an inventor.

129
00:07:50,840 --> 00:07:52,240
I previously read an interview

130
00:07:52,240 --> 00:07:54,100
with Tang Zhongming in 'Lihpao'.

131
00:07:54,240 --> 00:07:55,640
Actually, in 1931,

132
00:07:55,760 --> 00:07:57,820
he successfully built a modified car

133
00:07:57,880 --> 00:08:00,720
with a charcoal substitute oil furnace.

134
00:08:01,120 --> 00:08:02,040
He said at the time

135
00:08:02,040 --> 00:08:04,440
that he didn't build cars to make a fortune,

136
00:08:04,960 --> 00:08:08,640
but to break free from the monopoly of international oil merchants,

137
00:08:08,640 --> 00:08:09,970
so that our cars in China

138
00:08:10,360 --> 00:08:11,520
wouldn't turn into a pile of scrap metal

139
00:08:11,520 --> 00:08:13,180
just because there is no fuel.

140
00:08:13,880 --> 00:08:15,210
So when I first got here.

141
00:08:15,560 --> 00:08:17,680
When I saw that scrapped car,

142
00:08:17,760 --> 00:08:19,520
I thought about the principles of building one,

143
00:08:19,520 --> 00:08:20,680
so I decided to try it myself.

144
00:08:20,680 --> 00:08:21,810
That's impressive.

145
00:08:22,600 --> 00:08:25,120
I hope one day

146
00:08:25,760 --> 00:08:29,020
we can drive a charcoal car together to fight the Japanese.

147
00:08:30,480 --> 00:08:32,280
Then we need to build it quickly.

148
00:08:49,480 --> 00:08:51,560
Why did you open it? Seriously.

149
00:08:53,160 --> 00:08:55,280
I just thought if the stove stays covered,

150
00:08:55,280 --> 00:08:56,240
wouldn't the fire go out?

151
00:08:56,240 --> 00:08:57,840
Smoldering is exactly what I want.

152
00:08:57,840 --> 00:08:58,720
If the fire is too big,

153
00:08:58,720 --> 00:09:00,380
won't all the heat dissipate?

154
00:09:09,800 --> 00:09:12,320
Have you ever cooked or started a fire?

155
00:09:12,360 --> 00:09:13,160
No.

156
00:09:13,880 --> 00:09:16,760
When it comes to lighting a stove, you can't beat me.

157
00:09:19,040 --> 00:09:20,300
What are you doing now?

158
00:09:26,960 --> 00:09:27,600
Look.

159
00:09:31,320 --> 00:09:33,320
Smart. That works.

160
00:09:33,920 --> 00:09:37,080
You always say the army and the people are the foundation of victory.

161
00:09:37,080 --> 00:09:38,720
You are the army, and I am the people.

162
00:09:38,720 --> 00:09:41,800
You need to make use of folk wisdom.

163
00:09:42,200 --> 00:09:43,080
You're right.

164
00:09:43,640 --> 00:09:45,770
We're organizing a militia in Haiwen.

165
00:09:46,160 --> 00:09:47,360
This means we can't just rely on

166
00:09:47,360 --> 00:09:48,720
the military theory I learned before

167
00:09:48,720 --> 00:09:50,800
and all my accumulated combat experience.

168
00:09:50,800 --> 00:09:54,000
We need a deep understanding of people's livelihoods.

169
00:09:54,560 --> 00:09:55,960
So, Comrade Han Xiaoyue,

170
00:09:56,160 --> 00:09:58,560
please give me more guidance in the future.

171
00:09:59,240 --> 00:10:00,160
It's nothing.

172
00:10:01,560 --> 00:10:02,320
But

173
00:10:03,480 --> 00:10:05,610
you have to teach me how to ride a horse.

174
00:10:05,800 --> 00:10:06,720
Okay.

175
00:10:16,280 --> 00:10:17,080
Chef Meng,

176
00:10:17,640 --> 00:10:18,600
you have a guest.

177
00:10:18,920 --> 00:10:19,600
A guest?

178
00:10:20,480 --> 00:10:21,200
What guest?

179
00:10:21,280 --> 00:10:23,080
I don't know. It's a gentleman.

180
00:10:24,520 --> 00:10:25,720
Okay, I got it.

181
00:10:25,760 --> 00:10:26,360
All right.

182
00:10:29,960 --> 00:10:32,890
That day was the Mid-Autumn Festival on August 15th.

183
00:10:33,280 --> 00:10:36,140
It was my first time spending it on the battlefield.

184
00:10:36,680 --> 00:10:40,240
The brothers of our 87th Brigade were in the trenches,

185
00:10:41,160 --> 00:10:45,800
eating mooncakes made from water caltrops by Buddy Wanfu.

186
00:10:46,280 --> 00:10:49,480
Looking at the moon, we all felt a bit homesick.

187
00:10:51,080 --> 00:10:54,240
So I took the lead and sang a folk tune from Northeast China,

188
00:10:54,240 --> 00:10:55,880
'Crescent Moon Before Dawn'.

189
00:10:55,880 --> 00:10:57,800
Once I started, we couldn't stop.

190
00:10:58,160 --> 00:10:59,480
The brothers from Shanxi

191
00:10:59,480 --> 00:11:01,480
sang their Shanxi folk tunes.

192
00:11:02,120 --> 00:11:05,080
The brothers from Rehe sang their Rehe opera.

193
00:11:05,440 --> 00:11:08,500
The brothers from Shanghai sang their Shanghai songs.

194
00:11:08,560 --> 00:11:11,690
While we were singing, our brigade commander came over.

195
00:11:11,960 --> 00:11:12,880
We cheered

196
00:11:13,240 --> 00:11:15,840
and asked the brigade commander to sing for us.

197
00:11:17,560 --> 00:11:21,280
It was our first time seeing the brigade commander act shy.

198
00:11:21,720 --> 00:11:22,560
He said,

199
00:11:23,880 --> 00:11:27,480
My father once taught me a chant,

200
00:11:29,640 --> 00:11:30,970
and I still remember it.

201
00:11:32,080 --> 00:11:34,400
When will there be a bright moon?

202
00:11:35,080 --> 00:11:37,360
I ask the blue sky with wine in hand.

203
00:11:38,080 --> 00:11:41,320
I don't know what year it is

204
00:11:41,920 --> 00:11:44,400
in the celestial palaces today.

205
00:11:45,640 --> 00:11:48,320
That's exactly it. I taught him that.

206
00:11:48,520 --> 00:11:52,040
But none of us had ever heard chanting before.

207
00:11:52,160 --> 00:11:53,920
The brigade commander's singing

208
00:11:53,920 --> 00:11:55,880
really wasn't that pleasant to the ear.

209
00:11:55,880 --> 00:11:57,840
We didn't know what to do,

210
00:11:57,920 --> 00:11:59,320
so we just froze there.

211
00:12:01,600 --> 00:12:03,400
Yunkui has always sung like that.

212
00:12:03,400 --> 00:12:04,130
To be honest,

213
00:12:04,360 --> 00:12:06,600
he never sang well with me.

214
00:12:07,280 --> 00:12:09,400
Here, please have some egg drop soup.

215
00:12:10,080 --> 00:12:10,740
Please sit.

216
00:12:10,880 --> 00:12:11,560
Madam, sit.

217
00:12:11,760 --> 00:12:14,560
Careful, it's hot. This is to clear internal heat.

218
00:12:14,720 --> 00:12:15,200
Please.

219
00:12:20,600 --> 00:12:21,480
Smells good.

220
00:12:22,960 --> 00:12:24,480
Keep talking.

221
00:12:26,040 --> 00:12:31,080
The brigade commander probably felt we were down.

222
00:12:31,240 --> 00:12:32,880
And somehow,

223
00:12:33,000 --> 00:12:35,280
he started humming "The River All Red".

224
00:12:37,280 --> 00:12:46,000
♪ My wrath bristles in my helmet, as I lean against the railing ♪

225
00:12:46,160 --> 00:12:51,960
♪ The pattering rain has ceased ♪

226
00:12:52,440 --> 00:12:56,760
♪ I raise my eyes ♪

227
00:12:57,120 --> 00:13:00,680
♪ Towards the skies, I heave long sighs ♪

228
00:13:00,920 --> 00:13:03,960
We all sang along with him.

229
00:13:06,040 --> 00:13:12,640
♪ For the capital ♪

230
00:13:13,000 --> 00:13:15,560
But as we sang,

231
00:13:15,960 --> 00:13:18,160
our brothers

232
00:13:20,040 --> 00:13:21,840
were gone.

233
00:13:34,800 --> 00:13:36,960
All killed in battle.

234
00:13:38,920 --> 00:13:39,600
Wanfu,

235
00:13:40,080 --> 00:13:41,880
look who's here.

236
00:13:42,200 --> 00:13:44,840
He was also your brigade commander's subordinate,

237
00:13:44,840 --> 00:13:48,280
your brother-in-arms from the same trench.

238
00:13:48,520 --> 00:13:50,280
Wanfu, here's the thing.

239
00:13:50,520 --> 00:13:51,080
After I saw you

240
00:13:51,080 --> 00:13:52,920
and knew Master and Madam lived here,

241
00:13:52,920 --> 00:13:54,560
I really couldn't sit still.

242
00:13:54,880 --> 00:13:56,010
So I didn't tell you,

243
00:13:56,040 --> 00:13:58,000
and just came to see Master and Madam.

244
00:13:58,000 --> 00:13:59,460
You don't blame me, do you?

245
00:13:59,720 --> 00:14:01,280
You know I would.

246
00:14:01,800 --> 00:14:04,760
Huang, you shouldn't have come here.

247
00:14:04,880 --> 00:14:05,840
Do you know that the entire Tian Mansion

248
00:14:05,840 --> 00:14:07,960
doesn't know Master's true identity?

249
00:14:07,960 --> 00:14:08,880
Wanfu.

250
00:14:09,400 --> 00:14:11,520
We can hide it from outsiders,

251
00:14:11,920 --> 00:14:15,120
but there's no need to do so with Mr. Huang.

252
00:14:15,280 --> 00:14:17,240
Yes, Mr. Huang also told us

253
00:14:17,280 --> 00:14:18,740
many things about Yunkui.

254
00:14:19,360 --> 00:14:20,490
We love to hear them.

255
00:14:20,520 --> 00:14:21,200
Yes.

256
00:14:22,320 --> 00:14:23,480
Mr. Huang, please have a seat.

257
00:14:23,480 --> 00:14:24,720
Please sit, Madam.

258
00:14:25,320 --> 00:14:27,680
The day you were singing in the trench,

259
00:14:28,000 --> 00:14:30,400
sirens suddenly went off in Nanjing City.

260
00:14:31,080 --> 00:14:33,600
Yueming hadn't even been born then.

261
00:14:33,680 --> 00:14:35,010
He was still in my belly.

262
00:14:35,280 --> 00:14:38,520
Master and I hid in an air raid shelter.

263
00:14:38,640 --> 00:14:41,520
There were many people in the shelter.

264
00:14:42,080 --> 00:14:44,480
So many people shared a few mooncakes.

265
00:14:45,280 --> 00:14:47,320
We ate the mooncakes

266
00:14:47,600 --> 00:14:49,060
while looking at the moon,

267
00:14:49,080 --> 00:14:53,120
wondering where Yunkui was,

268
00:14:53,240 --> 00:14:54,800
if he was okay,

269
00:14:54,880 --> 00:14:56,120
and if he was injured.

270
00:14:56,920 --> 00:14:59,560
You looked at the moon in the trench,

271
00:15:00,080 --> 00:15:02,200
and we looked at the moon in the shelter.

272
00:15:02,200 --> 00:15:04,840
Even though we weren't together,

273
00:15:05,320 --> 00:15:06,040
but

274
00:15:06,840 --> 00:15:09,440
we were looking at the same moon, right?

275
00:15:10,840 --> 00:15:11,640
Mr. Huang,

276
00:15:12,040 --> 00:15:14,040
you and Yunkui are both heroes.

277
00:15:14,120 --> 00:15:15,560
Great heroes.

278
00:15:15,760 --> 00:15:17,200
I admire you.

279
00:15:17,320 --> 00:15:18,040
Master,

280
00:15:18,240 --> 00:15:21,680
our brigade commander is the real hero.

281
00:15:22,040 --> 00:15:24,120
Seeing the young master today,

282
00:15:25,320 --> 00:15:28,320
and seeing Madam and Master are doing well

283
00:15:28,440 --> 00:15:31,400
and healthy, I'm truly happy.

284
00:15:31,760 --> 00:15:34,000
I'm happy for our brigade commander.

285
00:15:34,120 --> 00:15:35,320
Huang,

286
00:15:40,920 --> 00:15:42,450
if you have any conscience,

287
00:15:42,920 --> 00:15:44,360
you should stay far away from Master.

288
00:15:44,360 --> 00:15:45,420
Don't drag us down.

289
00:15:45,840 --> 00:15:47,080
What are you talking about?

290
00:15:47,080 --> 00:15:48,680
You shouldn't talk like that.

291
00:15:48,680 --> 00:15:50,000
Master, Madam.

292
00:15:50,400 --> 00:15:53,320
It's my fault.

293
00:15:54,000 --> 00:15:55,000
I'm useless.

294
00:15:55,480 --> 00:15:56,840
Even now, I still rely on

295
00:15:57,000 --> 00:15:59,040
fortune-telling to make a living.

296
00:15:59,720 --> 00:16:01,560
Wanfu looks down on me.

297
00:16:01,720 --> 00:16:02,600
No, you...

298
00:16:02,840 --> 00:16:03,880
Mr. Huang...

299
00:16:04,760 --> 00:16:06,560
You don't need to be embarrassed.

300
00:16:06,560 --> 00:16:08,560
A hero is a hero, no matter his origin.

301
00:16:08,560 --> 00:16:10,720
Zhang Zifang and Liu Bowen

302
00:16:10,880 --> 00:16:13,320
were both fortune-tellers back then,

303
00:16:13,600 --> 00:16:16,040
but they still stabilized the country,

304
00:16:16,160 --> 00:16:18,020
and did great things in the world.

305
00:16:18,320 --> 00:16:20,440
I am deeply gratified

306
00:16:20,640 --> 00:16:23,160
that Mr. Huang could come to see me today.

307
00:16:23,600 --> 00:16:24,560
Wanfu,

308
00:16:24,880 --> 00:16:27,080
you guys are buddies in the same trench.

309
00:16:27,080 --> 00:16:28,720
You should visit each other often in the future

310
00:16:28,720 --> 00:16:30,280
and help each other out.

311
00:16:30,440 --> 00:16:31,880
Of course, Master.

312
00:16:32,200 --> 00:16:35,240
Wanfu and I are good buddies for life.

313
00:16:36,720 --> 00:16:38,320
Master, I want to tell you

314
00:16:38,320 --> 00:16:40,600
about our brigade commander at Baijiazhai.

315
00:16:40,600 --> 00:16:41,640
Do you want to hear it?

316
00:16:41,640 --> 00:16:43,080
Yes, I do.

317
00:16:43,360 --> 00:16:46,160
As long as it's about your brigade commander,

318
00:16:46,320 --> 00:16:47,880
and places he has been to,

319
00:16:48,000 --> 00:16:50,760
I will never get tired of hearing it.

320
00:16:50,920 --> 00:16:52,560
Never ever.

321
00:16:52,840 --> 00:16:53,520
Yujiao,

322
00:16:53,600 --> 00:16:55,440
hurry and get a pen and paper.

323
00:16:55,560 --> 00:16:58,160
Write it down carefully.

324
00:16:58,400 --> 00:17:00,520
When Yueming grows up in the future,

325
00:17:00,800 --> 00:17:03,160
you must tell him every word.

326
00:17:03,320 --> 00:17:04,119
Okay.

327
00:17:05,240 --> 00:17:06,170
Please sit down.

328
00:17:06,960 --> 00:17:07,920
Master,

329
00:17:09,040 --> 00:17:10,599
the battle at Baijiazhai

330
00:17:10,960 --> 00:17:12,720
was so tragic.

331
00:17:13,920 --> 00:17:15,599
But we won.

332
00:17:16,119 --> 00:17:19,000
The brigade commander led us to victory.

333
00:17:24,079 --> 00:17:25,210
Madam, please stay.

334
00:17:25,280 --> 00:17:26,680
I will come see you another day.

335
00:17:26,680 --> 00:17:27,880
Thank you, Mr. Huang.

336
00:17:31,040 --> 00:17:32,320
I'll see him out.

337
00:17:40,240 --> 00:17:41,760
What on earth do you want to do?

338
00:17:41,760 --> 00:17:44,640
What's wrong? You can take care of the brigade commander's family,

339
00:17:44,640 --> 00:17:46,240
but I can't come to visit?

340
00:17:49,800 --> 00:17:52,320
They are catching Anti-Japanese elements all over Shanghai now.

341
00:17:52,320 --> 00:17:53,320
Are you here to visit the Master,

342
00:17:53,320 --> 00:17:55,040
or to cause us trouble?

343
00:17:55,560 --> 00:17:57,560
If you want to kill him, I won't stop you.

344
00:17:57,560 --> 00:17:59,360
But don't drag us into it.

345
00:17:59,560 --> 00:18:00,320
Wanfu.

346
00:18:00,520 --> 00:18:01,920
You are a cook now.

347
00:18:02,520 --> 00:18:05,560
It's easy to put something in his food.

348
00:18:05,920 --> 00:18:07,120
Just this one thing,

349
00:18:07,200 --> 00:18:08,960
if you succeed, you are a hero who eliminates traitors,

350
00:18:08,960 --> 00:18:10,760
a hero who will go down in history.

351
00:18:10,760 --> 00:18:11,490
Don't worry.

352
00:18:11,840 --> 00:18:14,080
I will be responsible for the rest of the brigade commander's family's life.

353
00:18:14,080 --> 00:18:14,960
Bah.

354
00:18:15,720 --> 00:18:16,980
You have your mission,

355
00:18:17,200 --> 00:18:18,560
and I have my conscience.

356
00:18:18,560 --> 00:18:20,160
I am telling you clearly now,

357
00:18:20,960 --> 00:18:22,320
I will not betray you,

358
00:18:22,680 --> 00:18:24,160
but I won't help you either.

359
00:18:24,160 --> 00:18:25,000
Get out.

360
00:18:27,160 --> 00:18:29,240
Mr. Tian lives in that room, right?

361
00:18:29,320 --> 00:18:30,800
This house is really big.

362
00:18:30,880 --> 00:18:32,520
There are many doors and many roads.

363
00:18:32,520 --> 00:18:34,040
It's easy for someone to come in.

364
00:18:34,040 --> 00:18:37,120
Huang, what on earth do you want?

365
00:18:38,080 --> 00:18:39,360
Meng Wanfu,

366
00:18:40,000 --> 00:18:42,240
I don't have time to chat with you.

367
00:18:42,480 --> 00:18:44,810
You already know my identity and mission.

368
00:18:44,960 --> 00:18:46,120
Don't push me.

369
00:18:47,240 --> 00:18:51,080
I'm just asking you, are you going to do this or not?

370
00:18:52,640 --> 00:18:53,520
Huang,

371
00:18:54,120 --> 00:18:56,720
how dare you threaten me with a gun in this yard.

372
00:18:56,760 --> 00:18:57,680
I...

373
00:19:02,240 --> 00:19:03,720
If you don't want the people in this yard

374
00:19:03,720 --> 00:19:06,800
to know that you are a spy from the Bureau of Investigation and Statistics,

375
00:19:06,800 --> 00:19:07,720
work for me.

376
00:19:20,360 --> 00:19:23,200
Why are you pushing me like this, Huang?

377
00:19:23,400 --> 00:19:24,480
Do I owe you?

378
00:19:24,880 --> 00:19:26,560
If it weren't for you

379
00:19:26,840 --> 00:19:28,680
chasing me down the street, nagging,

380
00:19:28,680 --> 00:19:30,940
I wouldn't have been caught and drafted.

381
00:19:31,200 --> 00:19:32,240
Good for you.

382
00:19:32,400 --> 00:19:34,000
Some died, some ran away.

383
00:19:34,240 --> 00:19:36,920
I have to take care of the brigade commander's family, three generations.

384
00:19:36,920 --> 00:19:38,840
Do you know how much I've suffered?

385
00:19:38,840 --> 00:19:40,920
I finally managed to sneak into the Tian family,

386
00:19:40,920 --> 00:19:42,320
and have a few comfortable days.

387
00:19:42,320 --> 00:19:43,840
Then you pop up out of nowhere,

388
00:19:43,840 --> 00:19:44,760
can't get rid of you,

389
00:19:44,760 --> 00:19:46,560
forcing me to help you murder and commit arson.

390
00:19:46,560 --> 00:19:48,640
Why should I? Do I owe you?

391
00:19:49,040 --> 00:19:51,100
Did I owe you in a past life or this one?

392
00:19:51,720 --> 00:19:53,280
Come on, shoot.

393
00:19:53,600 --> 00:19:54,480
Shoot me.

394
00:19:54,800 --> 00:19:56,260
If you don't dare to shoot,

395
00:19:56,520 --> 00:19:58,650
then get out of here through that door.

396
00:20:00,840 --> 00:20:02,000
If you dare to shoot,

397
00:20:02,880 --> 00:20:06,120
do it now. Shoot me from behind.

398
00:20:11,000 --> 00:20:11,840
Shoot.

399
00:20:44,840 --> 00:20:45,960
Mr. Tian.

400
00:20:58,120 --> 00:20:59,240
Mr. Tian.

401
00:21:15,200 --> 00:21:16,120
Mr. Tian.

402
00:21:17,200 --> 00:21:18,520
Has Ms. Zeng left?

403
00:21:21,120 --> 00:21:24,600
Ms. Zeng was sent away safely.

404
00:21:27,520 --> 00:21:28,440
But,

405
00:21:31,320 --> 00:21:32,520
Qi is dead.

406
00:21:35,120 --> 00:21:36,780
The police station found out.

407
00:21:37,480 --> 00:21:38,960
He shot himself.

408
00:21:40,520 --> 00:21:42,240
So as not to be recognized,

409
00:21:43,880 --> 00:21:45,880
and not implicate the Tian Mansion,

410
00:21:46,840 --> 00:21:47,920
he used a gun

411
00:21:49,920 --> 00:21:53,200
to ruin his own face.

412
00:22:08,880 --> 00:22:10,280
Shouldn't I have left him

413
00:22:10,800 --> 00:22:11,840
all alone

414
00:22:12,920 --> 00:22:14,680
in that police station,

415
00:22:14,760 --> 00:22:16,840
in the cold morgue?

416
00:22:17,560 --> 00:22:19,080
I should bring him back.

417
00:22:19,800 --> 00:22:21,520
He grew up with me.

418
00:22:22,280 --> 00:22:24,240
I should bring him home, right?

419
00:22:25,520 --> 00:22:27,400
So what if it implicates the Tian Mansion?

420
00:22:27,400 --> 00:22:31,360
So what if it implicates me, Tian Jiatai?

421
00:22:38,360 --> 00:22:40,040
I will bring him back.

422
00:22:40,440 --> 00:22:42,120
Mr. Tian. Mr. Tian.

423
00:22:42,680 --> 00:22:43,480
Mr. Tian.

424
00:22:45,360 --> 00:22:47,290
Qi has already ruined his own face.

425
00:22:47,320 --> 00:22:48,320
If you go now,

426
00:22:48,640 --> 00:22:50,440
wouldn't his efforts be in vain?

427
00:22:55,960 --> 00:22:57,840
Qi cannot die in vain.

428
00:23:26,800 --> 00:23:27,720
Hello.

429
00:23:29,480 --> 00:23:32,520
Kudo, this is Tian Jiatai.

430
00:23:32,960 --> 00:23:36,640
Could you please come to my house tomorrow?

431
00:23:36,880 --> 00:23:38,400
Let's meet.

432
00:23:39,480 --> 00:23:42,200
I want to renegotiate our cooperation.

433
00:23:43,240 --> 00:23:44,040
Yes.

434
00:23:47,560 --> 00:23:48,840
It's a deal.

435
00:23:53,720 --> 00:23:56,440
Ms. Zeng was right.

436
00:23:57,040 --> 00:24:00,100
Holding on and waiting for a change will get us nowhere.

437
00:24:00,160 --> 00:24:02,880
Our so-called holding on is meaningless now.

438
00:24:03,520 --> 00:24:06,280
I will change and seek it myself.

439
00:24:06,880 --> 00:24:08,400
The last time Qi saw me,

440
00:24:08,440 --> 00:24:11,600
he firmly opposed me tearing down the factory and smuggling.

441
00:24:11,600 --> 00:24:14,760
But I think he would agree now.

442
00:24:16,440 --> 00:24:18,000
He should agree now.

443
00:24:37,000 --> 00:24:38,660
I will sit with you for a while.

444
00:26:07,560 --> 00:26:09,320
Wanfu, are you there?

445
00:26:16,880 --> 00:26:18,200
Not sleeping so late,

446
00:26:19,040 --> 00:26:20,840
what are you doing sitting here?

447
00:26:21,320 --> 00:26:22,450
I am waiting for you.

448
00:26:22,800 --> 00:26:23,600
What's wrong?

449
00:26:23,800 --> 00:26:25,200
I want to talk to you.

450
00:26:30,120 --> 00:26:31,040
Speak.

451
00:26:32,880 --> 00:26:34,000
Tomorrow morning,

452
00:26:35,120 --> 00:26:36,880
I will resign from Tian.

453
00:26:38,360 --> 00:26:39,490
Where are you going?

454
00:26:39,720 --> 00:26:40,680
It's not just me.

455
00:26:40,840 --> 00:26:43,840
You, Master, and Yueming,

456
00:26:44,160 --> 00:26:45,560
we are leaving together.

457
00:26:46,000 --> 00:26:47,260
Did something happen?

458
00:26:47,360 --> 00:26:48,640
I came here to work

459
00:26:48,880 --> 00:26:51,600
just to give you, Master,

460
00:26:51,640 --> 00:26:53,640
and Yueming a place to settle down.

461
00:26:54,880 --> 00:26:57,410
But now we can't stay in Tian Mansion anymore.

462
00:26:59,040 --> 00:27:01,570
Is it related to that Mr. Huang who came today?

463
00:27:03,160 --> 00:27:05,160
Tian Mansion is very dangerous now.

464
00:27:05,320 --> 00:27:07,050
This place is a nest of trouble.

465
00:27:07,200 --> 00:27:08,530
You should listen to me.

466
00:27:08,600 --> 00:27:10,920
Wanfu, when you and that Mr. Huang

467
00:27:11,000 --> 00:27:13,530
were struggling, I felt something was wrong.

468
00:27:14,160 --> 00:27:16,840
Is it about him? Who is he?

469
00:27:16,960 --> 00:27:18,080
Don't worry about it.

470
00:27:18,080 --> 00:27:19,280
Just come with me.

471
00:27:19,320 --> 00:27:20,960
Wanfu, tell me the truth.

472
00:27:21,200 --> 00:27:23,480
What is he here for? Who is he?

473
00:27:28,960 --> 00:27:30,160
He's from Chongqing.

474
00:27:30,720 --> 00:27:34,520
He's from the Bureau of Investigation and Statistics, here to eliminate traitors.

475
00:27:34,520 --> 00:27:36,320
He's here to kill Mr. Tian.

476
00:27:39,040 --> 00:27:41,160
Then why are you sitting here?

477
00:27:41,360 --> 00:27:42,080
Come with me.

478
00:27:42,080 --> 00:27:43,340
Let's go find Mr. Tian.

479
00:27:46,200 --> 00:27:48,330
Why are you still calling him Mr. Tian?

480
00:27:48,560 --> 00:27:50,680
He's a traitor, can't you see?

481
00:27:50,800 --> 00:27:52,860
He mixes with the Japanese every day.

482
00:27:52,960 --> 00:27:54,480
He's a smooth operator, slick.

483
00:27:54,480 --> 00:27:56,560
He will get into trouble sooner or later.

484
00:27:56,560 --> 00:27:58,200
Don't worry about him anymore.

485
00:27:58,200 --> 00:27:59,460
Worry about yourself.

486
00:27:59,520 --> 00:28:00,600
Worry about Master.

487
00:28:00,600 --> 00:28:02,360
Worry about Yueming.

488
00:28:02,760 --> 00:28:03,720
As for me,

489
00:28:04,080 --> 00:28:06,000
I can't stay here for another minute anyway.

490
00:28:06,000 --> 00:28:08,160
I don't even want to cook a meal for this traitor.

491
00:28:08,160 --> 00:28:10,080
He is not that kind of person, Wanfu.

492
00:28:10,080 --> 00:28:10,840
He is not that kind of person.

493
00:28:10,840 --> 00:28:12,700
You know what kind of person he is?

494
00:28:12,960 --> 00:28:15,400
Last time at Zengshou Restaurant, I was there.

495
00:28:15,400 --> 00:28:16,840
He was clearly not injured,

496
00:28:16,840 --> 00:28:18,520
but he came back injured.

497
00:28:18,640 --> 00:28:20,320
Who knows if he's really injured

498
00:28:20,320 --> 00:28:21,400
or faking it?

499
00:28:21,480 --> 00:28:24,520
Who knows what he's playing at?

500
00:28:26,120 --> 00:28:27,080
Also,

501
00:28:27,800 --> 00:28:29,960
recently you haven't even let me go to the second floor.

502
00:28:29,960 --> 00:28:31,360
Every day in that dark room,

503
00:28:31,360 --> 00:28:32,560
muttering.

504
00:28:32,640 --> 00:28:34,400
I don't even know what you're doing.

505
00:28:34,400 --> 00:28:37,160
Yes, you know best what you're doing.

506
00:28:37,680 --> 00:28:39,080
Is reading so addictive?

507
00:28:39,280 --> 00:28:40,480
Can't you just openly

508
00:28:40,480 --> 00:28:41,520
read in the study?

509
00:28:41,640 --> 00:28:43,200
Can't you read in the lounge?

510
00:28:43,200 --> 00:28:45,560
Must you read in that dark room?

511
00:28:47,040 --> 00:28:51,120
Madam, I don't know since when

512
00:28:51,640 --> 00:28:53,800
we became so distant.

513
00:28:54,400 --> 00:28:56,600
Since we came to Shanghai from Nanjing,

514
00:28:56,600 --> 00:28:58,200
how much hardship have we suffered along the way?

515
00:28:58,200 --> 00:29:00,600
Even when we fought Zhang Yunqi in the concession,

516
00:29:00,600 --> 00:29:02,440
we argued, but arguments aside,

517
00:29:02,520 --> 00:29:03,160
I always felt

518
00:29:03,160 --> 00:29:05,280
we were comrades in the same trench.

519
00:29:05,440 --> 00:29:06,600
But this time,

520
00:29:07,440 --> 00:29:10,760
ever since you finished reading to that Tian,

521
00:29:11,120 --> 00:29:12,960
you haven't told me anything.

522
00:29:13,200 --> 00:29:14,360
I don't see you in the morning.

523
00:29:14,360 --> 00:29:15,720
I don't see you at night.

524
00:29:15,920 --> 00:29:17,000
It's so hard to see you,

525
00:29:17,000 --> 00:29:19,000
and when I turn around, you're gone.

526
00:29:19,760 --> 00:29:21,840
It's like I'm nothing but a fart.

527
00:29:22,280 --> 00:29:24,440
Even Yueming's fart smells.

528
00:29:24,520 --> 00:29:25,160
I, a living person,

529
00:29:25,160 --> 00:29:27,160
walking around in front of you,

530
00:29:28,080 --> 00:29:30,040
am just like air.

531
00:29:35,640 --> 00:29:36,640
Not worth it.

532
00:29:37,960 --> 00:29:40,760
I feel it's not worth it for our brigade commander.

533
00:29:42,320 --> 00:29:44,000
That's why I'm leaving.

534
00:29:44,200 --> 00:29:45,240
Who wants to leave?

535
00:29:45,240 --> 00:29:47,240
No, I just want to leave.

536
00:29:48,200 --> 00:29:50,000
Aren't you going to miss Master?

537
00:29:51,720 --> 00:29:53,580
Aren't you going to miss Yueming?

538
00:30:01,280 --> 00:30:02,880
I'm just a little bug.

539
00:30:04,080 --> 00:30:05,600
Who would I miss?

540
00:30:06,920 --> 00:30:08,320
And who would miss me?

541
00:30:14,520 --> 00:30:16,450
You said I never tell you anything.

542
00:30:17,800 --> 00:30:20,920
If I tell you now, will you listen?

543
00:30:25,000 --> 00:30:25,880
Tell me.

544
00:30:26,320 --> 00:30:27,240
First,

545
00:30:29,120 --> 00:30:30,680
this is about Ms. Zeng.

546
00:30:31,760 --> 00:30:34,080
I helped Ms. Zeng at the charity sale before.

547
00:30:34,080 --> 00:30:35,360
During the sale,

548
00:30:35,480 --> 00:30:37,610
Ms. Zeng was wounded by a Japanese spy.

549
00:30:38,160 --> 00:30:40,840
The gunshot wound was right next to her heart.

550
00:30:40,960 --> 00:30:42,120
She bled a lot.

551
00:30:42,480 --> 00:30:44,140
I was very anxious at the time.

552
00:30:44,160 --> 00:30:46,240
But which hospital or clinic

553
00:30:46,320 --> 00:30:48,650
would take a patient with a gunshot wound?

554
00:30:49,160 --> 00:30:51,280
Mr. Tian sent Qi

555
00:30:51,360 --> 00:30:53,290
to bring Ms. Zeng into the mansion.

556
00:30:53,720 --> 00:30:54,720
During this time,

557
00:30:54,960 --> 00:30:56,120
Ms. Zeng has been hiding

558
00:30:56,120 --> 00:30:58,320
and recovering in Mr. Tian's darkroom.

559
00:30:58,920 --> 00:31:00,560
You said you couldn't see me

560
00:31:02,000 --> 00:31:03,800
because I was taking care of her.

561
00:31:04,400 --> 00:31:06,400
Not many people can know about this.

562
00:31:07,200 --> 00:31:09,040
With so many people in the mansion,

563
00:31:09,040 --> 00:31:10,960
only Mr. Tian, Qi, and I

564
00:31:11,120 --> 00:31:12,200
know about this.

565
00:31:12,920 --> 00:31:13,850
I didn't tell you

566
00:31:15,480 --> 00:31:18,010
because I didn't want to put you in danger too.

567
00:31:20,600 --> 00:31:21,400
Second,

568
00:31:22,200 --> 00:31:24,840
why did I come back so late tonight?

569
00:31:27,040 --> 00:31:32,160
Today, Qi escorted Ms. Zeng out of Shanghai.

570
00:31:32,520 --> 00:31:33,560
At the pier,

571
00:31:36,000 --> 00:31:37,720
they ran into Japanese spies.

572
00:31:38,800 --> 00:31:39,760
Qi...

573
00:31:43,000 --> 00:31:44,320
Qi is gone.

574
00:31:48,560 --> 00:31:49,680
Gone.

575
00:31:51,360 --> 00:31:55,040
Qi... Qi is dead.

576
00:32:01,200 --> 00:32:01,840
Qi grew up

577
00:32:01,920 --> 00:32:04,200
with Mr. Tian.

578
00:32:04,360 --> 00:32:07,120
I saw that Mr. Tian was really upset,

579
00:32:07,760 --> 00:32:09,360
so I sat with him for a while.

580
00:32:13,040 --> 00:32:15,680
Third, and most importantly,

581
00:32:15,880 --> 00:32:18,000
Mr. Tian's willingness to save Ms. Zeng

582
00:32:18,000 --> 00:32:20,480
shows that he's not a traitor.

583
00:32:20,920 --> 00:32:22,440
He's not what you said.

584
00:32:23,400 --> 00:32:25,120
So if he's in danger,

585
00:32:25,640 --> 00:32:27,400
shouldn't we help him?

586
00:32:29,200 --> 00:32:30,880
But Mr. Tian told me

587
00:32:31,160 --> 00:32:34,880
that he has something very big and important to do later,

588
00:32:35,240 --> 00:32:38,240
and asked us to leave Tian Mansion as soon as possible.

589
00:32:39,560 --> 00:32:41,880
I also wanted to come and discuss with you,

590
00:32:41,880 --> 00:32:43,320
in this situation,

591
00:32:44,880 --> 00:32:46,200
can we leave?

592
00:32:47,000 --> 00:32:50,880
What is Mr. Tian going to do?

593
00:33:48,800 --> 00:33:49,680
What?

594
00:33:50,120 --> 00:33:51,960
I heard you ring the bell.

595
00:33:52,200 --> 00:33:53,440
I was calling Qi.

596
00:33:53,800 --> 00:33:54,760
I know.

597
00:33:56,240 --> 00:33:57,520
Qi is dead.

598
00:33:58,520 --> 00:34:01,040
Madam told me everything last night.

599
00:34:03,840 --> 00:34:05,280
Don't blame Madam.

600
00:34:05,640 --> 00:34:08,440
It was because I wanted to resign and leave yesterday.

601
00:34:08,440 --> 00:34:09,440
Because these days,

602
00:34:09,440 --> 00:34:11,520
you wouldn't even let me go to the second floor.

603
00:34:11,520 --> 00:34:12,840
You and Madam were in the darkroom,

604
00:34:12,840 --> 00:34:15,040
and I didn't know what you were whispering about.

605
00:34:15,040 --> 00:34:16,840
Instead, you got closer and closer to the Japanese,

606
00:34:16,840 --> 00:34:18,400
and even did business with them.

607
00:34:18,400 --> 00:34:20,320
I thought you were a traitor.

608
00:34:21,000 --> 00:34:23,199
I didn't want to cook for a traitor anymore,

609
00:34:23,199 --> 00:34:24,639
so I wanted to resign.

610
00:34:24,880 --> 00:34:27,239
But Madam told me everything

611
00:34:27,360 --> 00:34:29,020
you did these past few months.

612
00:34:31,560 --> 00:34:33,040
I didn't sleep all night.

613
00:34:33,600 --> 00:34:34,800
I'm sorry, Master.

614
00:34:35,960 --> 00:34:37,199
I misunderstood you.

615
00:34:37,480 --> 00:34:40,520
So you are here to apologize?

616
00:34:41,760 --> 00:34:44,040
I... I just apologized.

617
00:34:44,120 --> 00:34:45,320
I said I'm sorry.

618
00:34:45,800 --> 00:34:47,199
I want to tell you

619
00:34:49,080 --> 00:34:50,340
that I want to help you.

620
00:34:50,480 --> 00:34:51,360
Help me?

621
00:34:52,560 --> 00:34:53,560
Help me with what?

622
00:34:54,320 --> 00:34:54,960
Help me

623
00:34:54,960 --> 00:34:57,840
learn to cook Cantonese cuisine, Hunan cuisine,

624
00:34:58,040 --> 00:35:00,100
Sichuan cuisine, and Anhui cuisine?

625
00:35:00,840 --> 00:35:01,760
No, Master.

626
00:35:02,160 --> 00:35:03,360
I am a cook,

627
00:35:03,720 --> 00:35:05,520
but the person talking to you right now

628
00:35:05,520 --> 00:35:06,920
is not a cook.

629
00:35:07,040 --> 00:35:09,600
I just want to tell you who I am.

630
00:35:10,080 --> 00:35:11,120
Who are you?

631
00:35:11,640 --> 00:35:12,760
I am Meng Wanfu.

632
00:35:13,240 --> 00:35:15,200
I am a soldier of the 87th Brigade,

633
00:35:16,000 --> 00:35:17,240
a deserter.

634
00:35:18,000 --> 00:35:19,330
I was originally a cook,

635
00:35:19,800 --> 00:35:21,460
but I was conscripted by them,

636
00:35:21,520 --> 00:35:23,720
and I went to the Shanghai Battlefield.

637
00:35:24,400 --> 00:35:25,880
All my brothers,

638
00:35:27,640 --> 00:35:29,100
they all charged forward,

639
00:35:29,800 --> 00:35:31,200
only I hid back.

640
00:35:32,040 --> 00:35:33,880
Our brigade commander is Zhang Yunkui.

641
00:35:33,880 --> 00:35:37,120
He is the most indomitable man I have ever seen.

642
00:35:37,640 --> 00:35:40,600
We were in Liu Town, he fought bravely against the enemy,

643
00:35:40,600 --> 00:35:43,200
until there were only the two of us left.

644
00:35:43,320 --> 00:35:45,920
Before he died, he gave his General's sword to me.

645
00:35:45,920 --> 00:35:47,580
He told me to take it to Nanjing

646
00:35:47,680 --> 00:35:49,080
and give it to his father.

647
00:35:49,200 --> 00:35:52,760
Yes, his father is Master,

648
00:35:52,800 --> 00:35:54,840
Madam is his widow,

649
00:35:54,920 --> 00:35:56,520
and Yueming is his son.

650
00:35:56,640 --> 00:35:58,080
In order to take care of his family,

651
00:35:58,080 --> 00:35:59,640
we pretended to be a family

652
00:35:59,720 --> 00:36:01,320
and lived in your house.

653
00:36:02,000 --> 00:36:05,280
You should know all this by now.

654
00:36:10,040 --> 00:36:12,640
Fulfill the commission and be loyal to the mission.

655
00:36:12,640 --> 00:36:14,080
In such a chaotic world,

656
00:36:14,280 --> 00:36:15,280
it's rare.

657
00:36:15,840 --> 00:36:16,840
You are good.

658
00:36:18,840 --> 00:36:20,080
I am not good at all.

659
00:36:21,880 --> 00:36:23,360
To tell the truth, when I got the sword,

660
00:36:23,360 --> 00:36:25,840
I didn't want to go to Nanjing at all.

661
00:36:26,400 --> 00:36:28,800
I just wanted to go to Wuhan to find Xiaoyue.

662
00:36:29,360 --> 00:36:31,360
Xiaoyue is my fiancée.

663
00:36:31,520 --> 00:36:33,400
When I was walking at that crossroads,

664
00:36:33,400 --> 00:36:34,320
I was hesitating.

665
00:36:34,320 --> 00:36:35,840
Should I go or not?

666
00:36:35,880 --> 00:36:37,640
I even wanted to throw the sword away.

667
00:36:37,640 --> 00:36:38,640
At that moment, a crow

668
00:36:38,640 --> 00:36:39,080
cawed

669
00:36:39,080 --> 00:36:40,240
and flew over my head,

670
00:36:40,240 --> 00:36:41,680
pooping on my shoulder.

671
00:36:41,760 --> 00:36:42,960
I was terrified.

672
00:36:43,240 --> 00:36:45,000
Was I being punished by heaven?

673
00:36:45,280 --> 00:36:46,400
What goes around comes around.

674
00:36:46,400 --> 00:36:48,200
I understood this principle.

675
00:36:48,440 --> 00:36:50,440
So I made up my mind

676
00:36:50,800 --> 00:36:52,200
and went to Nanjing.

677
00:36:52,520 --> 00:36:54,360
I met Madam and Master.

678
00:36:54,560 --> 00:36:55,720
I gave the sword to them.

679
00:36:55,720 --> 00:36:57,920
But I still wanted to go to Wuhan.

680
00:36:58,200 --> 00:36:59,800
So I boarded a ship to Wuhan.

681
00:37:00,000 --> 00:37:00,800
But as soon as I got on,

682
00:37:00,800 --> 00:37:02,440
I realized I took the wrong bundle.

683
00:37:02,440 --> 00:37:04,280
The brigade commander's sword was still in my hands.

684
00:37:04,280 --> 00:37:06,040
I tried to find a way to return it to them quickly.

685
00:37:06,040 --> 00:37:07,600
But right after I got on a small boat,

686
00:37:07,600 --> 00:37:08,640
that ship to Wuhan

687
00:37:08,680 --> 00:37:10,080
was bombed by the Japanese.

688
00:37:10,080 --> 00:37:12,680
I ended up boarding a ship to Shanghai in a daze.

689
00:37:12,880 --> 00:37:14,560
I followed them to Shanghai,

690
00:37:14,760 --> 00:37:15,720
and entered the concession.

691
00:37:15,720 --> 00:37:16,560
After entering the concession,

692
00:37:16,560 --> 00:37:18,240
I ran into Zhang Yunqi and his wife.

693
00:37:18,240 --> 00:37:19,120
I kept fighting with them.

694
00:37:19,120 --> 00:37:20,920
We fought constantly,

695
00:37:21,000 --> 00:37:21,860
back and forth.

696
00:37:21,880 --> 00:37:24,200
We even got Master thrown into prison.

697
00:37:24,280 --> 00:37:26,000
Then I found you.

698
00:37:26,560 --> 00:37:28,040
You saved Master.

699
00:37:28,760 --> 00:37:30,520
As for what happened next,

700
00:37:31,720 --> 00:37:33,200
you already know.

701
00:37:33,600 --> 00:37:35,440
I don't know why,

702
00:37:35,560 --> 00:37:36,420
but heaven just

703
00:37:36,480 --> 00:37:39,040
intertwined our lives.

704
00:37:40,320 --> 00:37:41,000
Sir.

705
00:37:41,400 --> 00:37:42,920
I've rambled on so much

706
00:37:43,000 --> 00:37:45,520
just to let you know

707
00:37:45,840 --> 00:37:47,800
what kind of person I am.

708
00:37:49,120 --> 00:37:50,320
I understand.

709
00:37:53,280 --> 00:37:54,400
You are a good man.

710
00:37:55,080 --> 00:37:57,200
I also know you want to help me.

711
00:37:57,920 --> 00:38:00,280
But what I have to do

712
00:38:00,920 --> 00:38:02,720
might not be as easy as you think.

713
00:38:03,320 --> 00:38:04,440
I'm also worried.

714
00:38:04,680 --> 00:38:06,120
You think this way now.

715
00:38:06,440 --> 00:38:09,360
What if you run into a crow later,

716
00:38:09,880 --> 00:38:11,540
and it poops on your shoulder?

717
00:38:11,680 --> 00:38:14,080
Will you change your mind again? So...

718
00:38:14,440 --> 00:38:16,360
I won't, sir.

719
00:38:17,920 --> 00:38:19,380
Madam told me everything.

720
00:38:19,840 --> 00:38:21,200
You don't want your factory

721
00:38:21,200 --> 00:38:22,600
to make a single bullet for the Japanese.

722
00:38:22,600 --> 00:38:24,360
You want to tear down the factory.

723
00:38:24,360 --> 00:38:26,090
You are doing such a huge thing.

724
00:38:28,160 --> 00:38:30,280
I figure you definitely need some help.

725
00:38:30,280 --> 00:38:33,200
Wanfu, I'm begging you.

726
00:38:33,680 --> 00:38:37,360
Other than you and Madam,

727
00:38:37,720 --> 00:38:39,720
I don't want a third person to know.

728
00:38:40,200 --> 00:38:41,320
You are very loyal.

729
00:38:41,640 --> 00:38:43,480
So just keep your promise.

730
00:38:43,840 --> 00:38:46,280
I appreciate your kindness.

731
00:38:46,800 --> 00:38:47,680
But,

732
00:38:47,960 --> 00:38:49,480
Qi is already dead.

733
00:38:50,040 --> 00:38:51,760
I don't want to get you killed

734
00:38:52,080 --> 00:38:53,600
because of me.

735
00:38:55,640 --> 00:38:56,680
Why bother?

736
00:38:57,360 --> 00:38:59,360
That sword back then,

737
00:39:00,680 --> 00:39:02,680
you could have thrown it away.

738
00:39:02,840 --> 00:39:04,600
Now you want to leave,

739
00:39:05,040 --> 00:39:06,280
then just go.

740
00:39:06,640 --> 00:39:07,520
Why bother?

741
00:39:27,080 --> 00:39:31,160
Our brigade commander has such a nice family,

742
00:39:31,320 --> 00:39:33,400
and such a nice Madam.

743
00:39:36,000 --> 00:39:37,320
Why did he bother?

744
00:39:39,000 --> 00:39:41,240
You're such a wealthy man

745
00:39:41,600 --> 00:39:43,320
with such a large estate.

746
00:39:43,760 --> 00:39:45,240
Why do you bother?

747
00:40:10,480 --> 00:40:13,360
Master, what are your orders?

748
00:40:16,720 --> 00:40:17,440
Go,

749
00:40:18,400 --> 00:40:21,240
get me a steamed bun made from hard dough first.

750
00:40:47,040 --> 00:40:49,920
Slow down, slow down.

751
00:40:50,200 --> 00:40:51,080
Hurry up.

752
00:40:51,640 --> 00:40:53,840
Slow down, I still need to add charcoal.

753
00:40:54,440 --> 00:40:56,700
Riding your cart really strains my arms.

754
00:40:56,840 --> 00:40:59,080
Crank it faster! Make the fire bigger.

755
00:40:59,960 --> 00:41:00,760
Slow down.

756
00:41:02,080 --> 00:41:03,340
Is there any charcoal?

757
00:41:03,480 --> 00:41:04,360
I'm adding it.

758
00:41:04,480 --> 00:41:06,280
I'm adding charcoal. Slow down.

759
00:41:07,760 --> 00:41:08,880
Slow down.

760
00:41:19,200 --> 00:41:21,200
Xiaoyue, it's done.

761
00:41:21,440 --> 00:41:22,520
What?

762
00:42:19,360 --> 00:42:20,290
What did you tie?

763
00:42:20,320 --> 00:42:21,840
Did you tie a dead knot?

764
00:42:22,360 --> 00:42:23,920
I tied it the way you taught me.

765
00:42:23,920 --> 00:42:25,080
You wrapped this one wrong.

766
00:42:25,080 --> 00:42:27,340
Look, it's like you didn't wrap it at all.

767
00:42:27,800 --> 00:42:28,930
Let me tie it for you.

768
00:42:37,280 --> 00:42:40,010
Do you still remember the greetings I taught you?

769
00:42:40,320 --> 00:42:41,580
I remember all of them.

770
00:42:41,680 --> 00:42:43,120
Hello is 'Bonjour'.

771
00:42:43,360 --> 00:42:44,840
Thank you is 'Merci'.

772
00:42:45,080 --> 00:42:46,720
What do you mean, 'Merci'?

773
00:42:47,200 --> 00:42:48,000
Hello.

774
00:42:48,040 --> 00:42:48,880
Bonjour.

775
00:42:49,200 --> 00:42:50,040
Thank you.

776
00:42:50,040 --> 00:42:51,120
Merci.

777
00:42:52,000 --> 00:42:54,720
Merci.

778
00:42:55,120 --> 00:42:56,000
Merci.

779
00:42:56,120 --> 00:42:57,360
Right, merci.

780
00:42:57,520 --> 00:42:58,560
Merci.

781
00:42:58,800 --> 00:43:01,400
Right, and the one French people always say.

782
00:43:01,600 --> 00:43:02,960
C'est la vie.
